nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
— <ckpt_name> is where you select your local LLM of choice
— <max_ctx> defines the amount of tokens used as a memory. If lowered too much, the LLM would "forget" about the task before completing it.
   → 2048 works fine
— <gpu_layers> layers of the LLM to be handled by the gpu's VRAM
   → higher is better/faster
   → if you run out of memory, lower that number, if you have enough VRAM you can increase it to speed up processing.
— <n_threads> the amount of threads your CPU handles at once. Leaving it at the default of 8 works fine.

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
— <system_msg> defines the assistent profile and instruction 
— <max_tokens> sets the maximum length of the output
— <temperature> controls randomness of answers, increasing variety and creativity, in exchange for accuracy
— <top_p> impacts output length and also balances creativity/accuracy
— <top_k> caps the amount of tokens considered for each generated token to the k-amount most likely options
— <frequency_penalty> discourages repetitiveness
— <presence_penalty> encourages a wider scope of token consideration
— <repeat_penalty> should do the same as <frequency_penalty>
Enabling prompt enhancer can achieve more detailed prompts and might not need LLava enhancer.
